snippet.textDisplay:
I honestly think that the dog being David himself is a bit of a stretch. If the death seriously scarred him that much, it'd be hard for him to do it in the first place. If his mom's death was the event that sent him down the path of vengence, why would he then suddenly bring himself to do it? Especially since the Void exists beyond time and space, then would it even work? Would he know for certain killing his mother would stop it from happening? I doubt it, quite honestly.

So I have a new theory. Maybe since the Void remnants of the dog scattered in the real world, then wouldn't it be possible for the Void to just seep in and... maybe... adapt the likenesses of the house into the Void itself? And since the dog would have been another mere Zombie Void thing adapted into a game, then would it be too far of a stretch to say it decided to try and set it up to look like Arthur's childhood home? To bring him vivid memories of the tragic night? Remind him of his mother's death to try and weaken his resolve? It would make sense if it knew Arther (or David) in the past and knew he would be coming. So what better way to try and chip away his resolve... than reminding him of the life he once had.

snippet.textDisplay: Hey Mat Pat, I was wondering if you could do a theory on how pokeballs work. in a previous video you mentioned that the technology used could be pocket dimensions, but if that's the case, why do pokemon break out? How do they break out? Why does it only take three turns of the pokeball before it's caught? What keeps them in said pocket dimension? And even after they're caught, in Let's go Pikachu & Let's go Eevee, They were caught but were able to move the pokeball around, and even break out of it, even after they were caught. I also remember an episode of Pokemon where Ash breaks a pokeball or something. Does that mean that the pokemon is no longer yours? Anyway, I've had so many questions about pokeballs after I watched that video. And your theories are all pretty darn sound so if you could come up with something, I'd be VERY interested. Thanks.
